#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2062
msgid ""
"It looks like it has been corrupted, like the ones we encountered in the "
"swamp. But this time, the corruption feels... natural."
msgstr ""
"Parece que está corrompido, como los que encontramos en el pantano. Pero "
"esta vez la corrupción se siente… natural."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2066
msgid ""
"There must be some kind of mad wose in this forest corrupting neighboring "
"trees."
msgstr ""
"Debe haber algún tipo de wose loco en este bosque corrompiendo los árboles "
"vecinos."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2078
msgid "It looks like that tree was completely rotten."
msgstr "Parece que ese árbol estaba completamente podrido."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2082
msgid ""
"It must have been the mad wose that corrupted all the other trees. The "
"forest should be more peaceful now."
msgstr ""
"Debe haber sido el wose loco el que corrompió a todos los otros árboles. El "
"bosque debería estar más tranquilo ahora."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2086
msgid "Well, I mean, apart from the rest of the wildlife trying to kill us."
msgstr "Bueno, digo, aparte del resto de la fauna que intenta matarnos."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2099
msgid "There was a cyclops in the house."
msgstr "Había un cíclope en la casa."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2118
msgid "There are stairs going down into a tunnel."
msgstr "Hay escaleras que bajan a un túnel."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2128
msgid "It must be the flooded tunnels Oboavlidlu told us about."
msgstr "Deben ser los túneles inundados de los que nos habló Oboavlidlu."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2132
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2171
msgid "Should we go down there?"
msgstr "¿Deberíamos bajar ahí?"

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2134
msgid ""
"Yes, we should try to find the treasure hunters. Who knows what happened to "
"them?"
msgstr ""
"Sí, deberíamos intentar encontrar a los cazadores de tesoros. ¿Quién sabe "
"qué les pasó?"

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2162
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2201
msgid "No, we have no time for that. We need to go down the old temple road."
msgstr ""
"No, no tenemos tiempo para eso. Tenemos que bajar por el camino del viejo "
"templo."

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2173
msgid "Yes, let's see where it leads."
msgstr "Sí, veamos a dónde lleva."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2219
msgid "Let's continue. We need to reach Oof fortress as quickly as possible."
msgstr ""
"Sigamos. Tenemos que llegar a la fortaleza de Oof lo más rápido posible."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2233
msgid "How many walking trees are there in this forest?!"
msgstr "¡¿Cuántos árboles que caminan hay en este bosque?!"

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2242
msgid "There are a lot of trees, but not all of them are wose."
msgstr "Hay muchos árboles, pero no todos son woses."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2246
msgid ""
"On the plus side, as you have seen, the wose are quite slow, so we just need "
"to progress faster than they are coming for us."
msgstr ""
"Por el lado bueno, como vieron, los woses son bastante lentos, así que solo "
"necesitamos avanzar más rápido de lo que ellos vienen por nosotros."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2250
msgid ""
"Even better, if we could get rid of the wose that is spreading the "
"corruption to the forest, the trees should then leave us in peace."
msgstr ""
"Aún mejor, si pudiéramos deshacernos del wose que está esparciendo la "
"corrupción al bosque, los árboles deberían dejarnos en paz después."

#. [scenario], id=36_Old_Temple_Road
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:4
msgid "Old Temple Road"
msgstr "Camino del Templo Antiguo"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:33
msgid "Find the entrance of the old temple"
msgstr "Encontrar la entrada del templo antiguo"

#. [side], type=Deathlord LotI
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:595
msgid "Undead Leader"
msgstr "Líder no-muerto"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:641
msgid "The road seems to continue north. I assume the temple is in the forest."
msgstr ""
"El camino parece continuar al norte. Asumo que el templo está en el bosque."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:645
msgid "From what I recall, it is actually in a clearing."
msgstr "Por lo que recuerdo, en realidad está en un claro."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:649
msgid "Then I will be glad when we get out of this forest. It is oppressing."
msgstr "Entonces estaré contento cuando salgamos de este bosque. Es opresivo."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:668
msgid "Undead. What a surprise."
msgstr "No-muertos. Qué sorpresa."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:672
msgid "It is not like we were supposed to go fight a powerful necromancer."
msgstr "No es como si fuéramos a pelear contra un nigromante poderoso."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:676
msgid "At least, we know it is the right way..."
msgstr "Al menos sabemos que es el camino correcto..."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:680
msgid ""
"Let's try not to keep any undead behind us. I'm already afraid that they "
"will warn Isut about us, I would rather not have them attack us in the back "
"at the worst time."
msgstr ""
"Intentemos no dejar ningún no-muerto detrás de nosotros. Ya me preocupa que "
"le avisen a Isut sobre nosotros, preferiría no tenerlos atacándonos por la "
"espalda en el peor momento."

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:685
msgid "Find the entrance of the Old Temple"
msgstr "Encontrar la entrada del Templo Antiguo"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:690
msgid "Kill all undead"
msgstr "Matar a todos los no-muertos"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:717
msgid ""
"South-east: The Scavenger’s Trading Post\n"
"North: Oof Fortress"
msgstr ""
"Sureste: Puesto Comercial del Carroñero\n"
"Norte: Fortaleza Oof"

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:741
msgid "Look! It looks like the entrance of the Old Temple is here."
msgstr "¡Miren! Parece que la entrada del Templo Antiguo está aquí."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:761
msgid "We don't have more time to waste here. Let's go!"
msgstr "No tenemos más tiempo que perder aquí. ¡Vamos!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:765
msgid "We need to reach Oof's fortress before captain Soimaql get overwhelmed."
msgstr ""
"Tenemos que llegar a la fortaleza de Oof antes de que el capitán Soimaql sea "
"abrumado."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:769
msgid ""
"I'm a bit afraid of the tentacle guardians we were warned about, let's hope "
"we can cross without meeting them."
msgstr ""
"Tengo un poco de miedo de los guardianes de tentáculos de los que nos "
"advirtieron, esperemos poder cruzar sin encontrarlos."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:781
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:911
msgid "Wait for us! We are still fighting the undead here!"
msgstr "¡Espérennos! ¡Todavía estamos luchando contra los no-muertos aquí!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:803
msgid ""
"I don't see any more undead around here. I think we can continue safely."
msgstr ""
"No veo más no-muertos por aquí. Creo que podemos continuar con seguridad."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:807
msgid ""
"Well, I mean, as safely as we can with a necromancer and tentacle monsters "
"on our way."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, digo, tan seguros como podemos con un nigromante y monstruos de "
"tentáculos en el camino."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:811
msgid "Let's get into the Old Temple."
msgstr "Entremos al Templo Antiguo."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:827
msgid "I think we are lost. We should have stayed on the main road."
msgstr ""
"Creo que nos perdimos. Deberíamos habernos quedado en el camino principal."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:831
msgid "Now, we will arrive too late to save captain Soimaql, and the kingdom."
msgstr ""
"Ahora llegaremos demasiado tarde para salvar al capitán Soimaql y al reino."

#. [scenario], id=37_Old_Temple
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:4
msgid "Old Temple"
msgstr "Templo Antiguo"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:27
msgid "Cross the old temple"
msgstr "Cruzar el templo antiguo"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:32
msgid "Defeat both enemy leaders"
msgstr "Derrotar a ambos líderes enemigos"

#. [objectives]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:45
msgid "Petrification can be healed in this scenario."
msgstr "La petrificación puede curarse en este escenario."

#. [side], type=Fury LoI
#. [unit_type], id=Fury LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:101 .\units\Fury.cfg:4
msgid "Fury"
msgstr "Furia"

#. [side], type=Mine Worm LoI
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:117
msgid "Worms"
msgstr "Gusanos"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:428
msgid ""
"So, this is the Old Temple. It looks like it was once majestic. But now it's "
"just... old"
msgstr ""
"Entonces, este es el Templo Antiguo. Parece que alguna vez fue majestuoso. "
"Pero ahora solo es... viejo."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:432
msgid ""
"Anyway, we need to cross it to reach Oof's fortress and save Captain "
"Soimaql. We must expect to have to fight a ``tentacle monster'', although I "
"have no idea what it might encompass."
msgstr ""
"De todos modos, tenemos que cruzarlo para llegar a la fortaleza de Oof y "
"salvar al capitán Soimaql. Debemos esperar tener que pelear contra un "
"«monstruo de tentáculos», aunque no tengo idea de qué pueda implicar eso."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:436
msgid "And undead. Undead too. Why not undead, indeed?..."
msgstr "Y no-muertos. No-muertos también. ¿Por qué no no-muertos, verdad?..."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:440
msgid ""
"I can feel a strong force of black magic north. There must be a powerful "
"necromancer there."
msgstr ""
"Siento una fuerte fuerza de magia negra al norte. Debe haber un nigromante "
"poderoso ahí."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:444
msgid ""
"If we believe in the reports, Isut must be at the fortress already, meaning "
"it is either one of his lackeys or one of his allies."
msgstr ""
"Si creemos en los informes, Isut ya debe estar en la fortaleza, lo que "
"significa que es uno de sus lacayos o uno de sus aliados."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:448
msgid ""
"I guess we will find out if we meet them. Although that would probably be a "
"good idea to defeat them: I would rather not have undead behind AND in front "
"of us."
msgstr ""
"Supongo que lo descubriremos si los encontramos. Aunque probablemente sería "
"buena idea derrotarlos: preferiría no tener no-muertos detrás y delante de "
"nosotros."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:473
msgid ""
"What's this monstrosity? It is a bit like a Mine Worm, but much bigger and "
"scarier."
msgstr ""
"¿Qué es esta monstruosidad? Se parece un poco a un Gusano Minero, pero mucho "
"más grande y aterrador."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:477
msgid "I am afraid it might be a beast called a Mehsi."
msgstr "Me temo que podría ser una bestia llamada Mehsi."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:481
msgid "Some scholars theorize it to be the adult form of the Mine Worm."
msgstr "Algunos eruditos teorizan que es la forma adulta del Gusano Minero."

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:485
msgid ""
"I refuse to believe that! Implying us dwarves have been struggling with mere "
"younglings for generation!"
msgstr ""
"¡Me niego a creer eso! ¡Implicando que nosotros los enanos hemos estado "
"luchando contra meros jóvenes durante generaciones!"

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:489
msgid "Bloody scholars! Disrespecting the entire dwarvish race."
msgstr "¡Malditos eruditos! ¡Faltándole el respeto a toda la raza enana!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:493
msgid ""
"Mine Worm or not, be careful everyone, because it looks like it could eat "
"any of us whole. Even a horse..."
msgstr ""
"Gusano Minero o no, cuidado todos, porque parece que podría comernos "
"enteros. Incluso a un caballo..."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:518
msgid ""
"So, this must be the famous tentacle monster. Be careful everyone one, it "
"made the legionary nearly mad."
msgstr ""
"Entonces, este debe ser el famoso monstruo de tentáculos. Cuidado todos, "
"volvió loco al legionario."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:534
msgid "Wait, there are two of them?!"
msgstr "¡Espera, hay dos de ellos!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:538
msgid ""
"Or could it be that those are not the tentacle monster and that something "
"even scarier is?"
msgstr ""
"¿O podría ser que esos no sean el monstruo de tentáculos y que haya algo aún "
"más aterrador?"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:562
msgid ""
"Oh! So, this is the tentacle monster! No wonder that poor legionary went mad "
"fleeing that thing."
msgstr ""
"¡Oh! Entonces, este es el monstruo de tentáculos. No es de extrañar que ese "
"pobre legionario se volviera loco huyendo de esa cosa."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:566
msgid ""
"Unlucky us, it looks like it's blocking the exit. I'm not sure we will be "
"able to pass without fighting it..."
msgstr ""
"Qué mala suerte, parece que está bloqueando la salida. No estoy seguro de "
"que podamos pasar sin pelear contra eso..."

#. [message], speaker=necromancer
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:586
msgid ""
"You may have found me, but you will never be able to defeat Mal Wlicikoyl, "
"Commander Isut's second in command."
msgstr ""
"Pueden haberme encontrado, pero nunca podrán derrotar a Mal Wlicikoyl, el "
"segundo al mando del Comandante Isut."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:590
msgid "Well, at least we know who we are facing."
msgstr "Bueno, al menos sabemos a quién enfrentamos."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:594
msgid ""
"It would be a great victory to defeat him as it would probably impair their "
"undead army."
msgstr ""
"Sería una gran victoria derrotarlo, ya que probablemente debilitaría su "
"ejército de no-muertos."

#. [message], speaker=necromancer
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:607
msgid "You may have defeated me, but never will you defeat Commander Isut!"
msgstr ""
"¡Pueden haberme derrotado a mí, pero nunca derrotarán al Comandante Isut!"

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:628
msgid "It looks like all the undead he was commanding are crumbling to dust."
msgstr ""
"Parece que todos los no-muertos que comandaba se están desmoronando en polvo."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:641
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:657
msgid "It looks like some undead are still standing."
msgstr "Parece que algunos no-muertos siguen en pie."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:645
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:661
msgid ""
"Those are probably directly controlled by Isut. There should not be many "
"that far from the fortress."
msgstr ""
"Esos probablemente están controlados directamente por Isut. No debería haber "
"muchos tan lejos de la fortaleza."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:678
msgid "That's it! We defeated the tentacle monster!"
msgstr "¡Listo! ¡Derrotamos al monstruo de tentáculos!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:687
msgid ""
"We might not have defeated the necromancer, but once we will have defeated "
"Isut, it should be easy for the Legion to clean the Temple."
msgstr ""
"Tal vez no hayamos derrotado al nigromante, pero una vez que derrotemos a "
"Isut, debería ser fácil para la Legión limpiar el Templo."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:691
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:707
msgid "Now, let's get out of here, find this Isut and save Captain Soimaql!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ahora salgamos de aquí, encontremos a Isut y salvemos al capitán Soimaql!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:703
msgid ""
"Now that we have defeated both the monster and the necromancer, people "
"should be able to use this way again once Isut is defeated."
msgstr ""
"Ahora que derrotamos tanto al monstruo como al nigromante, la gente debería "
"poder usar este camino de nuevo una vez que Isut sea derrotado."

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:44
msgid "Defeat Isut"
msgstr "Derrotar a Isut"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:53
msgid "Enter Oof's fortress"
msgstr "Entrar en la fortaleza de Oof"

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:65
msgid "Defeat all undead"
msgstr "Derrotar a todos los no-muertos"

#. [side], type=Draug
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:144
msgid "Undead Hordes"
msgstr "Hordas No-muertas"

#. [side], type=Dwarvish Steelclad
#. [side], type=Duelist
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:382
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:49
msgid "Defenders"
msgstr "Defensores"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:443
msgid "I'm glad to finally be out of this cave. It was oppressing."
msgstr "Me alegra por fin estar fuera de esta cueva. Era opresiva."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:447
msgid "Probably because of how old everything was in there."
msgstr "Probablemente por lo antiguo que era todo ahí dentro."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:451
msgid "And undead. Undead too. And tentacle monsters."
msgstr "Y no-muertos. No-muertos también. Y monstruos de tentáculos."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:455
msgid ""
"Anyway, we must not be far from the fortress now. We need to find Isut "
"quickly and defeat him before the fortress fall."
msgstr ""
"De todos modos, no debemos estar lejos de la fortaleza ahora. Tenemos que "
"encontrar a Isut rápido y derrotarlo antes de que la fortaleza caiga."

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:470
msgid "East: Oof Fortress"
msgstr "Este: Fortaleza Oof"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:488
msgid ""
"East: Oof Fortress, Scavenger’s Trading Post\n"
"West: Eastern Swamp"
msgstr ""
"Este: Fortaleza Oof, Puesto Comercial del Carroñero\n"
"Oeste: Pantano Oriental"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:507
msgid ""
"North: Oof Fortress\n"
"South: Scavenger’s Trading Post"
msgstr ""
"Norte: Fortaleza Oof\n"
"Sur: Puesto Comercial del Carroñero"

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:529
msgid "That wolf looks weird."
msgstr "Ese lobo se ve raro."

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:533
msgid ""
"It looks as if it was possessed. Or rather as if something was wearing a "
"wolf like a costume."
msgstr ""
"Parece como si estuviera poseído. O más bien como si algo estuviera usando "
"un lobo como disfraz."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:547
msgid "I found Isut!"
msgstr "¡Encontré a Isut!"

#. [message], speaker=Isut
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:557
msgid ""
"Finally, adversaries to match up to myself. I thought I would die from "
"boredom fighting those pathetic legionaries."
msgstr ""
"Por fin, adversarios a mi altura. Pensé que iba a morir de aburrimiento "
"peleando contra esos patéticos legionarios."

#. [message], speaker=Isut
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:561
msgid "We will see if you make better adversaries than the other humans."
msgstr "Veremos si ustedes son mejores adversarios que los otros humanos."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:585
msgid "Well, looks like we are trapped. Not like we intended to flee anyway."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, parece que estamos atrapados. No es que tuviéramos intención de huir "
"de todos modos."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:589
msgid "Fight!"
msgstr "¡Peleen!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:614
msgid "We did it! Isut is no more!"
msgstr "¡Lo logramos! ¡Isut ya no existe!"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:627
msgid "Aren't his undead supposed to fall into dust or something?"
msgstr ""
"¿No se supone que sus no-muertos deberían convertirse en polvo o algo así?"

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:631
msgid ""
"They should be. But I am not versed in orcish necromancy so I could be wrong."
msgstr ""
"Deberían. Pero no estoy versado en nigromancia orca, así que podría estar "
"equivocado."

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:635 .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:675
msgid ""
"They seems to wander aimlessly now at least, which means the fortress should "
"be safe."
msgstr ""
"Al menos ahora parecen vagar sin rumbo, lo que significa que la fortaleza "
"debería estar a salvo."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:639 .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:653
msgid "So, we did it?! We saved the fortress?! Hurray!"
msgstr "¡Entonces, lo logramos?! ¡Salvamos la fortaleza! ¡Hurra!"

#. [message], speaker=Teumiuxe, Csia
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:643 .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:657
msgid "We should go there to meet Captain Soimaql now."
msgstr "Deberíamos ir allá a encontrarnos con el capitán Soimaql ahora."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:647
msgid "Shouldn't we kill the remaining undead before?"
msgstr "¿No deberíamos matar a los no-muertos restantes antes?"

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:667
msgid "Aren't Isut undead supposed to haven fallen into dust or something?"
msgstr ""
"¿No se supone que los no-muertos de Isut deberían haberse convertido en "
"polvo o algo así?"

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:671
msgid ""
"They should have. But I am not versed in orcish necromancy so I could be "
"wrong."
msgstr ""
"Deberían haberlo hecho. Pero no estoy versado en nigromancia orca, así que "
"podría estar equivocado."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:679
msgid "We should probably kill the remain undead anyway."
msgstr ""
"Probablemente deberíamos matar a los no-muertos restantes de todos modos."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:696
msgid "I found something in the house."
msgstr "Encontré algo en la casa."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:734
msgid "I'm Ubidaiubua, a roving mage and a Traveler."
msgstr "Soy Ubidaiubua, un mago errante y un Viajero."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:749
msgid ""
"Thoze foolz couldn’t even recognize their mother…I’ve an exzellent magic "
"againzt the Ockz but thoze bloody legionariez don’t truzt me under the "
"pretext that I’m a Traveler, a ztranger!"
msgstr ""
"Esos tontos no podrían ni reconocer a su madre... Tengo una excelente magia "
"contra los Ockz pero esos malditos legionarios no confían en mí con el "
"pretexto de que soy un Viajero, un extraño!"

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:753
msgid "My couzin Bta is captive inside. I must make sure she’z alright."
msgstr "Mi prima Bta está cautiva adentro. Debo asegurarme de que esté bien."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:772
msgid "Maybe they will let me in if I’m with you… "
msgstr "Tal vez me dejen entrar si estoy con ustedes... "

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:776
msgid "I’m willing to zell my zpells to YOU, for 78000."
msgstr "Estoy dispuesto a vender mis hechizos a USTEDES, por 78000."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:780
msgid "Deal?"
msgstr "¿Trato?"

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:792
msgid "I am afraid you don't have enough gold for a mage like me."
msgstr "Me temo que no tienen suficiente oro para un mago como yo."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:815
msgid "I am zorry, but you zeem to be quite a party already."
msgstr "Lo ziento, pero parecen zer ya un grupo bastante grande."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:836
msgid "Ubidaiubua will remember you, pal! Thiz iz a promize!"
msgstr "¡Ubidaiubua los recordará, amigo! ¡Esto es una promesa!"

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:840
msgid "Let’z go in the fortrezz together and zee what thre’z to zee!"
msgstr "¡Entremos en la fortaleza juntos y veamos qué hay que ver!"

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:844
msgid "You can now recruit red mages."
msgstr "Ahora puedes reclutar magos rojos."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:857
msgid "Then, leave. You don’t trust Ubidaiubua."
msgstr "Entonces, váyanse. No confían en Ubidaiubua."

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:861
msgid "You’re not worthy of the zervicez of the wonderful roving mage I am."
msgstr "No son dignos de los servicios del maravilloso mago errante que soy."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:899
msgid "Here is the fortress. Let's meet Captain Soimaql."
msgstr "Aquí está la fortaleza. Vamos a conocer al Capitán Soimaql."

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:936
msgid "I think it was the last undead around."
msgstr "Creo que era el último no-muerto por aquí."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:940
msgid "Let's go to the fortress then."
msgstr "Entonces vamos a la fortaleza."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:1036
msgid "No! We arrive too late, the fortress has already fallen!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡Llegamos demasiado tarde, la fortaleza ya cayó!"

#. [scenario], id=39_Oofs_Fortress
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:4
msgid "Oof's Fortress"
msgstr "Fortaleza de Oof"

#. [part]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:15
msgid ""
"The greatest threat for Oof’s fortress disappeared with Isut death, but the "
"serious danger of the reappearance of this ancient malevolent spirit "
"seriously torments our hero."
msgstr ""
"La mayor amenaza para la fortaleza de Oof desapareció con la muerte de Isut, "
"pero el grave peligro de la reaparición de este antiguo espíritu maligno "
"atormenta seriamente a nuestro héroe."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:156
msgid "Excuse me, are you Captain Soimaql?"
msgstr "Disculpe, ¿es usted el capitán Soimaql?"

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:160
msgid ""
"I am. Thank you for saving what is left of the Legion that was defending the "
"fortress."
msgstr ""
"Soy yo. Gracias por salvar lo que queda de la Legión que estaba defendiendo "
"la fortaleza."

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:164
msgid ""
"One hundred and eighty-two dead… And all this because a dummy disobeyed "
"orders!"
msgstr ""
"Ciento ochenta y dos muertos… ¡Y todo esto porque un idiota desobedeció "
"órdenes!"

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:172
msgid ""
"A scout had noticed the Ocks in the wood several weeks ago, but he kept "
"quiet from fear that the others may accuse him of seeing ghosts."
msgstr ""
"Un explorador había notado a los Ocks en el bosque hace varias semanas, pero "
"guardó silencio por miedo a que los demás lo acusaran de ver fantasmas."

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:176
msgid "The Ocks?! Ain't they supposed to be all dead and buried for centuries?"
msgstr "¿¡Los Ocks!? ¿No se supone que llevan siglos muertos y enterrados?"

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:180
msgid ""
"Everybody believed those creatures had well and truly disappeared for three "
"centuries."
msgstr ""
"Todos creían que esas criaturas habían desaparecido de verdad hacía tres "
"siglos."

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Ancient_Dark_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Ancient Dark Wose"
msgstr "Wose Oscuro Antiguo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Ancient_Dark_Wose.cfg:16
msgid ""
"It has always been all too known to all creatures that nature is not only a "
"nurturing mother; it can also be cruel, violent and destructive. It's "
"unknown what makes a wose become corrupted, but one thing is certain: "
"nowhere else does nature's rage becomes more evident than in an Ancient Dark "
"Wose."
msgstr ""
"Siempre ha sido bien conocido por todas las criaturas que la naturaleza no "
"solo es una madre nutricia; también puede ser cruel, violenta y destructiva. "
"Se desconoce qué hace que un wose se corrompa, pero una cosa es cierta: en "
"ningún otro lugar la ira de la naturaleza se hace más evidente que en un "
"Wose Oscuro Antiguo."

#. [unit_type], id=Fury Scourge LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:4
msgid "Fury Scourge"
msgstr "Furia Azote"

#. [unit_type], id=Fury Scourge LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Fury Scourge are juvenile Furies. Although not as deadly as their adult "
"form, they can still petrify those who dare look at them."
msgstr ""
"Las Furias Azote son furias juveniles. Aunque no son tan mortales como su "
"forma adulta, aún pueden petrificar a quienes se atreven a mirarlas."

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:59 .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:73
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:91 .\units\Fury.cfg:105
msgid "petrify"
msgstr "petrificar"

#. [petrifies]
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:85
msgid ""
"Petrify:\n"
"This attack petrifies the target, turning it to stone. Units that have been "
"petrified may not move or attack. The effect will wear off after a turn."
msgstr ""
"Petrificar:\n"
"Este ataque petrifica al objetivo, convirtiéndolo en piedra. Las unidades "
"petrificadas no pueden moverse ni atacar. El efecto desaparece después de un "
"turno."

#. [unit_type], id=Deshra Juggernaut LoI, race=deshra
#: .\units\deshra_juggernaut.cfg:5
msgid "Deshra Juggernaut"
msgstr "Juggernaut Deshra"

#. [unit_type], id=Direrat LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Direrat.cfg:4
msgid "Direrat"
msgstr "Rata Terrible"

#. [unit_type], id=Direrat LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Direrat.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Much larger than the giant rats which often inhabit caves, these vermin can "
"injure an armed civilian, and can prove frustratingly aggressive on any "
"footing. On top of being notably very aggressive at night, these creatures "
"pose much of a threat to any serious fighter."
msgstr ""
"Mucho más grandes que las ratas gigantes que a menudo habitan en cuevas, "
"estos bichos pueden herir a un civil armado, y pueden resultar "
"frustrantemente agresivos en cualquier terreno. Además de ser notablemente "
"muy agresivos por la noche, estas criaturas representan una gran amenaza "
"para cualquier guerrero serio."

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Dragonguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Dragonguard.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Dragonguard"
msgstr "Guardia Dragón Gobot"

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Dragonguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Dragonguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"It is not clear why the Dragonguards are called what they are, a name stolen "
"from the dwarves. Some speculate that the name comes from their weapon of "
"choice, these strange staves that belch fire and death. Others have surmised "
"that it is because such weapons would be a threat against even a true "
"Dragon, should such a thing be seen again in the known world. Whatever the "
"case, it is for these weapons that the guardians of the great Goblin "
"citadels are both renowned and feared; weapons that have broken the "
"mightiest of warriors with a storm of blows."
msgstr ""
"No está claro por qué los Guardias Dragón se llaman así, un nombre robado de "
"los enanos. Algunos especulan que el nombre viene de su arma preferida, "
"estos extraños bastones que eructan fuego y muerte. Otros han supuesto que "
"es porque tales armas serían una amenaza incluso contra un verdadero Dragón, "
"si tal cosa se viera de nuevo en el mundo conocido. Sea como sea, es por "
"estas armas que los guardianes de las grandes ciudadelas goblin son tanto "
"renombrados como temidos; armas que han roto a los guerreros más poderosos "
"con una tormenta de golpes."

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Elder_Dark_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Elder Dark Wose"
msgstr "Wose Anciano Oscuro"

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Elder_Dark_Wose.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Filled with hatred and malice, these beings will destroy anything that is "
"foolish enough to stand in their way."
msgstr ""
"Llenos de odio y malicia, estos seres destruirán cualquier cosa lo "
"suficientemente imprudente como para interponerse en su camino."

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:4
msgid "race^Deshra"
msgstr "Deshra"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:5
msgid "race+female^Deshra"
msgstr "Deshra"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:6
msgid "race^Deshrai"
msgstr "Deshrai"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:12
msgid "The Deshra (literally "
msgstr "Los Deshra (literalmente "

#. [unit_type], id=Frozen Lich LoI, race=undead
#: .\units\Frozen_Lich.cfg:4
msgid "Frozen Lich"
msgstr "Liche Congelado"

#. [unit_type], id=Frozen Lich LoI, race=undead
#: .\units\Frozen_Lich.cfg:29
msgid ""
"A lich is the physical embodiment of black magic’s first goal: the quest to "
"achieve immortality. Though a great deal is sacrificed in the rebirth, in "
"becoming a lich one cheats death of that which truly gives it terror. For it "
"is the mind that is retained, and the spirit which follows, though the body "
"may wither away.\n"
"\n"
"It is not known, save perhaps by the inner circles of necromancy, whether "
"life is prolonged indefinitely or simply extended. The fact that this "
"question can be raised at all is a testament to the magnitude of what their "
"order has achieved.\n"
"\n"
"This lich transformed in the Ice Cave, conferring it specails powers based "
"on cold."
msgstr ""
"Un liche es la encarnación física del primer objetivo de la magia negra: la "
"búsqueda de la inmortalidad. Aunque se sacrifica mucho en el renacimiento, "
"al convertirse en un liche uno engaña a la muerte de aquello que "
"verdaderamente le da terror. Porque es la mente la que se retiene, y el "
"espíritu que la sigue, aunque el cuerpo pueda marchitarse.\n"
"\n"
"No se sabe, salvo quizás por los círculos internos de la nigromancia, si la "
"vida se prolonga indefinidamente o simplemente se extiende. El hecho de que "
"esta pregunta pueda plantearse es un testimonio de la magnitud de lo que su "
"orden ha logrado.\n"
"\n"
"Este liche se transformó en la Cueva de Hielo, confiriéndole poderes "
"especiales basados en el frío."

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: .\units\Frozen_Lich.cfg:45
msgid "cold touch"
msgstr "toque frío"

#. [unit_type], id=Fury LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Furies were once very beautiful beings, legend said that a man who looked at "
"them was not able to keep a clear mind because of their beauty. But when "
"they turned against the gods they were cursed and turned into monstrosities. "
"Their gaze is so terrible that any being looking at them will be paralyzed "
"in fear. They are sourrounded by a dark aura that weakens and kills enemies."
msgstr ""
"Las furias alguna vez fueron seres muy hermosos, la leyenda dice que un "
"hombre que las miraba no podía mantener la mente clara debido a su belleza. "
"Pero cuando se volvieron contra los dioses fueron maldecidas y convertidas "
"en monstruosidades. Su mirada es tan terrible que cualquier ser que las mire "
"quedará paralizado de miedo. Están rodeadas por un aura oscura que debilita "
"y mata a los enemigos."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:77
msgid "gaze"
msgstr "mirada"

#. [petrifies]
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:117
msgid ""
"Petrify:\n"
"This attack petrifies the target, turning it to stone. Units that have been "
"petrified may not move or attack. It will wear off after a turn."
msgstr ""
"Petrificar:\n"
"Este ataque petrifica al objetivo, convirtiéndolo en piedra. Las unidades "
"petrificadas no pueden moverse ni atacar. El efecto desaparece después de un "
"turno."

#. [unit_type], id=Green Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Green_Crystal.cfg:5
msgid "Green Crystal"
msgstr "Cristal Verde"

#. [unit_type], id=Green Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Green_Crystal.cfg:31
msgid ""
"A Green Crystal is a Shard that has emerged from a high concentration of "
"mana located in a cave.\n"
"\n"
"Crystals are bound to their mana geyser, so they cannot go out of the cave "
"they were born in. Crystals are crystalline in nature and so have unusual "
"resistances. A consequence of this is their immunity to Drain, Poison and "
"Plague."
msgstr ""
"Un Cristal Verde es un Fragmento que ha surgido de una alta concentración de "
"maná ubicada en una cueva.\n"
"\n"
"Los cristales están unidos a su géiser de maná, por lo que no pueden salir "
"de la cueva en la que nacieron. Los cristales son de naturaleza cristalina y "
"por eso tienen resistencias inusuales. Una consecuencia de esto es su "
"inmunidad al Drenaje, Veneno y Plaga."

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Grenadeer LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Grenadeer.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Grenadeer"
msgstr "Granadero Gobot"

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Grenadeer LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Grenadeer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This curious machine looks like a Dwarven Thunderguards made out of metal. "
"The Dwarven Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these "
"strange staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. "
"The machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the "
"grave by the dwarves of Knalga who wield them, and are assumed to have even "
"forged them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange "
"black dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel "
"the beast imprisoned within. It seems that goblins tried to replicate them, "
"leading to a strange machine able to shoot explosive spheres.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these ‘boomsticks’ can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the goblins as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""
"Esta curiosa máquina parece un Guardia Trueno Enano hecho de metal. Los "
"Guardias Trueno Enanos son famosos por su curiosa armería, estos extraños "
"bastones de madera y hierro que hacen un ruido ensordecedor en su ira. Las "
"maquinaciones detrás de esta armería son un misterio, un secreto llevado a "
"la tumba por los enanos de Knalga que los empuñan, y se asume que incluso "
"los forjaron. Lo más que se sabe son informes de enanos vertiendo un extraño "
"polvo negro en la boca de sus armas, que algunos dicen es comida para "
"alimentar a la bestia imprisoned dentro. Parece que los goblins intentaron "
"replicarlos, llevando a una extraña máquina capaz de disparar esferas "
"explosivas.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque un solo disparo de estos «bastones boom» puede tomar varios minutos "
"en prepararse, los resultados son vistos por los goblins como bien valiosos "
"la espera."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\Grenadeer.cfg:29
msgid "boomstick"
msgstr "bastón boom"

#. [unit_type], id=Hell Boar LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Hellboar.cfg:4
msgid "Hell Boar"
msgstr "Jabalí Infernal"

#. [unit_type], id=Hell Boar LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Hellboar.cfg:35
msgid ""
"It is said that those boars were bread by the Ocks to be used as yoke for "
"their wagons. Since those were vanquished, they found a place of residence "
"in the Black Forest, where they compete with bears for food."
msgstr ""
"Se dice que esos jabalíes fueron criados por los Ocks para usarlos como yugo "
"para sus carretas. Desde que aquellos fueron vencidos, encontraron un lugar "
"de residencia en el Bosque Negro, donde compiten con los osos por comida."

#. [unit_type], id=Diseased Herb Spirit LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\HerbDiseased.cfg:5
msgid "Diseased Herb Spirit"
msgstr "Espíritu de Hierba Enfermo"

#. [unit_type], id=Diseased Herb Spirit LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\HerbDiseased.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Most of the herb spirits use their power to repel insect infestations but a "
"few of them welcome the insects in so that they can use them as game pieces "
"or suddenly expel them as a method of attack."
msgstr ""
"La mayoría de los espíritus de hierba usan su poder para repeler "
"infestaciones de insectos, pero unos pocos los reciben para usarlos como "
"piezas de juego o expulsarlos repentinamente como método de ataque."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bat LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Bat.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Bat"
msgstr "Murciélago de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bat LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Bat.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The most vicious, predatory, and successful of the creatures born in the ice "
"cave."
msgstr ""
"La más viciosa, depredadora y exitosa de las criaturas nacidas en la cueva "
"de hielo."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Ice_Bat.cfg:37
msgid "ice fangs"
msgstr "colmillos de hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bowman LoI, race=elemental, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Bowman"
msgstr "Arquero de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bowman LoI, race=elemental, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Bowman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Born in the cold of the ice cave, ice bowmen are fearsome enemies. The great "
"strength allows them to attack with high range and power."
msgstr ""
"Nacidos en el frío de la cueva de hielo, los arqueros de hielo son enemigos "
"temibles. Su gran fuerza les permite atacar con alto alcance y poder."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\Ice_Bowman.cfg:37 .\units\Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:37
msgid "ice longbow"
msgstr "arco largo de hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Golem LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Golem.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Golem"
msgstr "Gólem de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Golem LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Golem.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Ice elementals, once gathering enough elemental essence, can absorb more ice "
"and grow larger and stronger. Although they are weak, they can take massive "
"amounts of damage before they are destroyed to shards."
msgstr ""
"Los elementales de hielo, una vez que reúnen suficiente esencia elemental, "
"pueden absorber más hielo y crecer más grandes y fuertes. Aunque son "
"débiles, pueden recibir cantidades masivas de daño antes de ser destruidos "
"en fragmentos."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Guard LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Guard.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Guard"
msgstr "Guardia de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Guard LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Guard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Ice Guards are picked from the best swordsmen in the ice cave. They function "
"as bodyguards and commanders. Their reliability and mastery of close combat "
"are their best assets, for which they are well-renowned."
msgstr ""
"Los Guardias de Hielo son elegidos de los mejores espadachines en la cueva "
"de hielo. Funcionan como guardaespaldas y comandantes. Su confiabilidad y "
"maestría en el combate cuerpo a cuerpo son sus mejores activos, por los que "
"son bien renombrados."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Ice_Guard.cfg:39
msgid "ice longsword"
msgstr "espada larga de hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Hero LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Hero.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Hero"
msgstr "Héroe Troll de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Hero LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Hero.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Some ice trolls are born with an exceptional share of the strength and "
"vitality that characterizes their race. In a society where might makes "
"right, those of their ilk revere them as heroes."
msgstr ""
"Algunos trolls de hielo nacen con una porción excepcional de la fuerza y "
"vitalidad que caracteriza a su raza. En una sociedad donde la fuerza hace el "
"derecho, aquellos de su tipo los reverencian como héroes."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Master Bowman LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Master Bowman"
msgstr "Maestro Arquero de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Master Bowman LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Born in the cold of the ice cave, ice master bowmen have reached the zenith "
"of their art, inasmuch as any ice bowman is capable. Armed with a great ice "
"bow, these warriors crown battalions of ice bowmen with their presence, "
"bringing down many a foe with their well-aimed shots. Of the many races in "
"the world, only the elves surpass them in archery, and their human "
"counterparts have speculated, perhaps in envy, that this is only by dint of "
"age."
msgstr ""
"Nacidos en el frío de la cueva de hielo, los maestros arqueros de hielo han "
"alcanzado el zenit de su arte, en la medida en que cualquier arquero de "
"hielo es capaz. Armados con un gran arco de hielo, estos guerreros coronan "
"batallones de arqueros de hielo con su presencia, derribando a muchos "
"enemigos con sus disparos bien apuntados. De las muchas razas en el mundo, "
"solo los elfos los superan en arquería, y sus contrapartes humanas han "
"especulado, quizás por envidia, que esto es solo por cuestión de edad."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Swordsman LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Swordsman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Swordsman"
msgstr "Espadachín de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Swordsman LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Swordsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Born into the cold of the icecave, this unit is an experienced warrior "
"equipped with a sturdy broadsword made of ice."
msgstr ""
"Nacido en el frío de la cueva de hielo, esta unidad es un guerrero "
"experimentado equipado con una robusta espada ancha hecha de hielo."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Ice_Swordsman.cfg:38
msgid "ice sword"
msgstr "espada de hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll"
msgstr "Troll de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved "
"from common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. A fully-grown ice "
"troll towers above a man, and, even unarmed, would be a great threat in "
"combat. The large clubs typically favored in fighting act as extensions of "
"their arms, used for the same purpose of mauling their prey into submission."
msgstr ""
"Los trolls de hielo han sido descubiertos recientemente. Se piensa que "
"evolucionaron de trolls comunes atrapados en una región de frío congelante. "
"Un troll de hielo completamente crecido se eleva por encima de un hombre, y, "
"incluso desarmado, sería una gran amenaza en combate. Los grandes garrotes "
"típicamente favorecidos en la lucha actúan como extensiones de sus brazos, "
"usados para el mismo propósito de mutilar a su presa hasta la sumisión."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Shaman LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Shaman"
msgstr "Chamán Troll de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Shaman LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved "
"from common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. Ice troll shamans "
"are the mystical leaders of the ice trolls. Though not as strong or tough as "
"other ice trolls, their true power lies in their cold magic, which they use "
"to blast enemies with gouts of ice or to hide in the frozen forests."
msgstr ""
"Los trolls de hielo han sido descubiertos recientemente. Se piensa que "
"evolucionaron de trolls comunes atrapados en una región de frío congelante. "
"Los chamanes troll de hielo son los líderes místicos de los trolls de hielo. "
"Aunque no tan fuertes o resistentes como otros trolls de hielo, su verdadero "
"poder radica en su magia fría, que usan para explotar a los enemigos con "
"chorros de hielo o para esconderse en los bosques congelados."

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:52
msgid "ice blast"
msgstr "explosión de hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Warrior LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Warrior"
msgstr "Guerrero Troll de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Warrior LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Warrior.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved "
"from common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. Ice trolls "
"typically neither need nor prefer to use any proper armament in combat, as "
"large ‘sticks and stones’ serve them all too well. However, ice trolls have "
"been seen on numerous occasions clad in rough-shod armor and bearing metal "
"hammers. It is speculated that orcish allies are the source and crafters of "
"these; expeditions into several forcibly-vacated ice troll caves have shown "
"little evidence of tool use, and certainly no metalworking of any kind. "
"Given how dangerous an ice troll is with its bare hands, the thought of one "
"with proper armament is entirely unsettling."
msgstr ""
"Los trolls de hielo han sido descubiertos recientemente. Se piensa que "
"evolucionaron de trolls comunes atrapados en una región de frío congelante. "
"Los trolls de hielo típicamente ni necesitan ni prefieren usar armamento "
"apropiado en combate, ya que grandes «palos y piedras» les sirven muy bien. "
"Sin embargo, los trolls de hielo han sido vistos en numerosas ocasiones "
"vestidos con armadura tosca y portando martillos de metal. Se especula que "
"aliados orcos son la fuente y artesanos de estos; expediciones a varias "
"cuevas de trolls de hielo evacuadas a la fuerza han mostrado poca evidencia "
"de uso de herramientas, y ciertamente ningún trabajo de metal. Dado lo "
"peligroso que es un troll de hielo con sus manos desnudas, el pensamiento de "
"uno con armamento apropiado es completamente inquietante."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wyvern LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Wyvern.cfg:8
msgid "Ice Wyvern"
msgstr "Wyvern de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wyvern LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Wyvern.cfg:49
msgid ""
"Wyverns are large reptiles that resemble dragons, but are not the "
"intelligent, magical creatures. However, the fact that they are just wild "
"beasts should not cause any traveler who encounters one to dismiss the "
"threat, for they are fast and fierce when threatened or hungry.\n"
"\n"
"Although wyverns are social creatures, usually traveling in pairs or small "
"groups, their icy counterpart seems to be of solitary nature. Their hunting "
"patterns and diet are difficult to discern, for they often work with smaller "
"animals that would appear to be potential prey. That odd behavior may be an "
"adaptation to the harsh icy environments they inhabit."
msgstr ""
"Los wyverns son grandes reptiles que se asemejan a dragones, pero no son las "
"criaturas inteligentes y mágicas. Sin embargo, el hecho de que sean solo "
"bestias salvajes no debería hacer que ningún viajero que encuentre uno "
"descarte la amenaza, ya que son rápidos y feroces cuando se les amenaza o "
"tienen hambre.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque los wyverns son criaturas sociales, usualmente viajando en parejas o "
"grupos pequeños, su contraparte helada parece ser de naturaleza solitaria. "
"Sus patrones de caza y dieta son difíciles de discernir, ya que a menudo "
"trabajan con animales más pequeños que parecerían ser presas potenciales. "
"Ese comportamiento extraño puede ser una adaptación a los entornos helados "
"ásperos que habitan."

#. [unit_type], id=Initiate, race=human
#: .\units\Mage_Initiate.cfg:5
msgid "Initiate"
msgstr "Iniciado"

#. [unit_type], id=Initiate, race=human
#: .\units\Mage_Initiate.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Initiates belong to the few individuals who are capable of using magic and "
"who had the luck of being discovered by a mage order. The amount of studying "
"that is still ahead of them may seem intimidating, but at the same time, the "
"mere existence of this knowledge is a testament to what humanity can "
"achieve.\n"
"\n"
"Initiates are helpless in melee combat, but possess great offensive "
"potential that will grow as they get more experienced."
msgstr ""
"Los iniciados pertenecen a los pocos individuos capaces de usar magia y que "
"tuvieron la suerte de ser descubiertos por una orden de magos. La cantidad "
"de estudio que aún les espera puede parecer intimidante, pero al mismo "
"tiempo, la mera existencia de este conocimiento es un testimonio de lo que "
"la humanidad puede lograr.\n"
"\n"
"Los iniciados son indefensos en combate cuerpo a cuerpo, pero poseen un gran "
"potencial ofensivo que crecerá a medida que ganen experiencia."

#. [female]
#: .\units\Mage_Initiate.cfg:81
msgid "female^Initiate"
msgstr "Iniciada"

#. [unit_type], id=Saurian Matriarch LoI, race=lizard, gender=female
#: .\units\Matriarch.cfg:4
msgid "female^Saurian Matriarch"
msgstr "Matriarca Sauria"

#. [unit_type], id=Mehsi LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:4
msgid "Mehsi"
msgstr "Mehsi"

#. [unit_type], id=Mehsi LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Mehsi incite fear and awe in miners and explorers, figuring often in "
"folklore as wrathful deities of the underground. Capable of destroying carts "
"effortlessly, and possessed of seemingly endless strength and vitality, "
"these elusive leviathans are destructive and relentless to any who try to "
"combat them. Generally living in the deep, Mehsi are imposing even to the "
"elite dwarven warriors, and are the reason they seldom inhabit tunnels close "
"to the surface."
msgstr ""
"Los Mehsi incitan miedo y asombro en mineros y exploradores, figurando a "
"menudo en el folclore como deidades iracundas del subsuelo. Capaces de "
"destruir carretas sin esfuerzo, y poseídos de una fuerza y vitalidad "
"aparentemente interminable, estos leviatanes elusivos son destructivos e "
"implacables con cualquiera que intente combatirlos. Generalmente viviendo en "
"lo profundo, los Mehsi son imponentes incluso para los guerreros enanos "
"élite, y son la razón por la que rara vez habitan túneles cerca de la "
"superficie."

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:28 .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:41
msgid "dig"
msgstr "cavar"

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:29 .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:42
msgid "female^dig"
msgstr "cavada"

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:30 .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:43
msgid ""
"This unit can hide underground, and remain undetected by its enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Enemy units cannot see this unit while it is underground, except if they "
"have units next to it. Any enemy unit that first discovers this unit "
"immediately loses all its remaining movement."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidad puede esconderse bajo tierra, y permanecer indetectada por sus "
"enemigos.\n"
"\n"
"Las unidades enemigas no pueden ver esta unidad mientras esté bajo tierra, "
"excepto si tienen unidades junto a ella. Cualquier unidad enemiga que "
"descubra primero esta unidad pierde inmediatamente todo su movimiento "
"restante."

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:33 .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:46
msgid ""
"On soft ground, this unit’s ambush skill renders it invisible to enemies "
"unless it is immediately adjacent or has revealed itself by attacking."
msgstr ""
"En terreno blando, la habilidad de emboscada de esta unidad la hace "
"invisible para los enemigos a menos que esté inmediatamente adyacente o se "
"haya revelado atacando."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:44 .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:57
msgid "stings"
msgstr "aguijones"

#. [unit_type], id=Mine Worm LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:4
msgid "Mine Worm"
msgstr "Gusano de Mina"

#. [unit_type], id=Mine Worm LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Scholars differ as to the ancestry of the Mine Worm. Some hold that they "
"were brought to the mine by the demons. Others hold that they have always "
"been here. What is certain is that it is wise to avoid mines where they are "
"known to congregate."
msgstr ""
"Los eruditos difieren en cuanto a la ascendencia del Gusano de Mina. Algunos "
"sostienen que fueron traídos a la mina por los demonios. Otros sostienen que "
"siempre han estado aquí. Lo que es cierto es que es sabio evitar minas donde "
"se sabe que se congregan."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Hole LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Hole"
msgstr "Agujero de Hielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Monolith Sword, race=elemental
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:82
msgid "Ice Monolith Sword"
msgstr "Monolito de Hielo Espada"

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:128
msgid "What the hell! That block of ice just turned into a swordsman."
msgstr ""
"¡Qué demonios! Ese bloque de hielo acaba de convertirse en un espadachín."

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Monolith Bow, race=elemental
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:161
msgid "Ice Monolith Bow"
msgstr "Monolito de Hielo Arco"

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:207
msgid "Great... Now there are ice blocks turning into archers too."
msgstr ""
"Genial... Ahora hay bloques de hielo convirtiéndose en arqueros también."

#. [unit_type], id=Purple Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Purple_Crystal.cfg:5
msgid "Purple Crystal"
msgstr "Cristal Púrpura"

#. [unit_type], id=Purple Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Purple_Crystal.cfg:31
msgid ""
"When too much mana concentrate in one place, a Purple Crystal natural "
"emerge. It is a sudden event, very different from the slow accumulation of "
"mana whose result is Green Crystals. \n"
"\n"
"Crystals are bound to their mana geyser, so they cannot go out of the cave "
"they were born in. Crystals are crystalline in nature and so have unusual "
"resistances. A consequence of this is their immunity to Drain, Poison and "
"Plague."
msgstr ""
"Cuando demasiado maná se concentra en un lugar, un Cristal Púrpura emerge "
"naturalmente. Es un evento repentino, muy diferente de la lenta acumulación "
"de maná cuyo resultado son Cristales Verdes. \n"
"\n"
"Los cristales están unidos a su géiser de maná, por lo que no pueden salir "
"de la cueva en la que nacieron. Los cristales son de naturaleza cristalina y "
"por eso tienen resistencias inusuales. Una consecuencia de esto es su "
"inmunidad al Drenaje, Veneno y Plaga."

#. [unit_type], id=Scorpion Soldier LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Scorpion_Soldier.cfg:4
msgid "Scorpion Soldier"
msgstr "Soldado Escorpión"

#. [unit_type], id=Scorpion Soldier LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Scorpion_Soldier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"A giant scorpion is highly dangerous. The deadliness of this one is beyond "
"imagination."
msgstr ""
"Un escorpión gigante es altamente peligroso. La letalidad de este está más "
"allá de la imaginación."

#. [unit_type], id=Spiderling LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Spiderling.cfg:4
msgid "Spiderling"
msgstr "Arañita"

#. [unit_type], id=Spiderling LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Spiderling.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Right after their birth, Giant Spiders, then called Spiderling, already have "
"a decent span, comparable in size to a Giant Scorpion. Although far less "
"dangerous than their adult form, they can already be a threat to surprised "
"adventurers due to their poisonous bite and their thick, sticky web."
msgstr ""
"Justo después de su nacimiento, las Arañas Gigantes, entonces llamadas "
"Arañitas, ya tienen un tamaño decente, comparable al de un Escorpión "
"Gigante. Aunque mucho menos peligrosas que su forma adulta, ya pueden ser "
"una amenaza para aventureros sorprendidos debido a su mordida venenosa y su "
"tela gruesa y pegajosa."

#. [unit_type], id=Tesla Coil LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Tesla_Coil.cfg:5
msgid "Tesla Coil"
msgstr "Bobina Tesla"

#. [unit_type], id=Tesla Coil LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Tesla_Coil.cfg:36
msgid ""
"High amounts of an unknown kind of energy are created in this machine, and "
"used in an unknown way somewhere else. You have pretty much no idea what "
"this thing is meant to do. The light it creates seems to harm everyone "
"nearby."
msgstr ""
"Altas cantidades de un tipo desconocido de energía se crean en esta máquina, "
"y se usan de manera desconocida en otro lugar. No tienen idea de qué se "
"supone que haga esta cosa. La luz que crea parece dañar a todos cerca."

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Thunderguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Thunderguard.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Thunderguard"
msgstr "Guardia Trueno Gobot"

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Thunderguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Thunderguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This curious machine looks like a Dwarven Thunderguards made out of metal. "
"The Dwarven Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these "
"strange staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. "
"The machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the "
"grave by the dwarves of Knalga who wield them, and are assumed to have even "
"forged them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange "
"black dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel "
"the beast imprisoned within. It seems that goblins tried to replicate them, "
"leading to a strange machine able to shoot lightnings.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these ‘thundersticks’ can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the goblins as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""
"Esta curiosa máquina parece un Guardia Trueno Enano hecho de metal. Los "
"Guardias Trueno Enanos son famosos por su curiosa armería, estos extraños "
"bastones de madera y hierro que hacen un ruido ensordecedor en su ira. Las "
"maquinaciones detrás de esta armería son un misterio, un secreto llevado a "
"la tumba por los enanos de Knalga que los empuñan, y se asume que incluso "
"los forjaron. Lo más que se sabe son informes de enanos vertiendo un extraño "
"polvo negro en la boca de sus armas, que algunos dicen es comida para "
"alimentar a la bestia imprisoned dentro. Parece que los goblins intentaron "
"replicarlos, llevando a una extraña máquina capaz de disparar rayos.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque un solo disparo de estos «bastones trueno» puede tomar varios minutos "
"en prepararse, los resultados son vistos por los goblins como bien valiosos "
"la espera."

#. [unit_type], id=Orcish Commander LoI, race=orc
#: .\units\Warlock.cfg:5
msgid "Orcish Commander"
msgstr "Comandante Orco"

#. [unit_type], id=Orcish Commander LoI, race=orc
#: .\units\Warlock.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Some orcish shamans prefer to abandon their order, or are just expelled from "
"it for various reasons. Such orcs live as hermits in uninhabited places such "
"as swamps or caves. during their exile, they sometimes study the local "
"flora, learning about the properties of some herbs. Occasionally, some of "
"them get bored with their hermit lifestyle, and decided to sell their "
"services to wealthy orcish warlord. Their knowliege of herbalism is heavily "
"valued amongs their employers. They usually aren't used to heal the "
"frontline, since orcish commanders prefer to use most their troops as cannon "
"fodder. They are mostly used if the warlord who employed them is injured, or "
"if the need to keep alive a certain troop is strategically critical."
msgstr ""
"Algunos chamanes orcos prefieren abandonar su orden, o simplemente son "
"expulsados de ella por varias razones. Tales orcos viven como ermitaños en "
"lugares deshabitados como pantanos o cuevas. Durante su exilio, a veces "
"estudian la flora local, aprendiendo sobre las propiedades de algunas "
"hierbas. Ocasionalmente, algunos se aburren de su estilo de vida ermitaño, y "
"deciden vender sus servicios a señores de la guerra orcos adinerados. Su "
"conocimiento de herboristería es altamente valorado entre sus empleadores. "
"Usualmente no se usan para sanar la línea frontal, ya que los comandantes "
"orcos prefieren usar la mayoría de sus tropas como carne de cañón. Se usan "
"principalmente si el señor de la guerra que los empleó está herido, o si la "
"necesidad de mantener viva una cierta tropa es estratégicamente crítica."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\Warlock.cfg:43
msgid "nature flare"
msgstr "destello natural"

#. [unit_type], id=Young Man LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Young_Man.cfg:4
msgid "Young Man"
msgstr "Hombre Joven"

#. [unit_type], id=Young Man LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Young_Man.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This Young Man has decided to go on an adventure. He was not trained to use "
"any weapon but is smart enough to understand how to use them. He can use "
"pitchforks, clubs, daggers and bows, but only one at a time. "
msgstr ""
"Este Hombre Joven ha decidido ir a una aventura. No fue entrenado para usar "
"ninguna arma pero es lo suficientemente inteligente para entender cómo "
"usarlas. Puede usar horquillas, garrotes, dagas y arcos, pero solo uno a la "
"vez. "

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Young_Man.cfg:95
msgid "knife"
msgstr "cuchillo"

#. [unit_type], id=Young Giant Spider LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Young_Spider.cfg:4
msgid "Young Giant Spider"
msgstr "Araña Gigante Joven"

#. [unit_type], id=Young Giant Spider LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Young_Spider.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Although the most encounter version is its adult form, Giant Spider are not "
"born directly as such. When they are born, they are called Spiderlings and "
"have a size similar to Giant Scorpions. They then metamorphose a first time "
"to become what we call Young Giant Spiders, that are twice the size of the "
"Spiderling, then a second time to become Giant Spiders. Although its younger "
"version tend to hide from sight, it is a formidable opponent that should not "
"be taken lightly."
msgstr ""
"Aunque la versión más encontrada es su forma adulta, las Arañas Gigantes no "
"nacen directamente como tales. Cuando nacen, se llaman Arañitas y tienen un "
"tamaño similar a los Escorpiones Gigantes. Luego metamorfosean una primera "
"vez para convertirse en lo que llamamos Arañas Gigantes Jóvenes, que son el "
"doble del tamaño de la Arañita, luego una segunda vez para convertirse en "
"Arañas Gigantes. Aunque su versión más joven tiende a esconderse de la "
"vista, es un oponente formidable que no debe tomarse a la ligera."

