#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4257
msgid "Biography of Buxo Iova"
msgstr "Biografía de Buxo Iova"

#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4262
msgid ""
"Buxo Iova has the distinction to have been declared dead more often than any "
"other soldier in the history of the 10th Legion. At Yooradweak’s pass, it "
"was said that goblin attackers had defeated him whereas he was beating them "
"to flight three days later. He was then declared dead in a snowstorm while "
"he was gone looking for Caprine, his beloved mule, to finally return, a week "
"later, starving and bothered by a hole in his shoe. \n"
"\n"
"For his allies, stories about his death are entertainment. For his enemies, "
"the object of their desire.  In his opinion, death will only bring him when "
"he will be bored or tired of life and the Reaper better bring "
"reinforcement! \n"
"\n"
"Brought up by a former cook of the 10th Legion, Buxo left to the west of "
"Idaamub as guide for the ofite synod at age 16. He later arrived at "
"Idaamub’s castle and shown a cover letter ordering he was given the position "
"of his mother, but he was found to be worse cook than soldier and he soon "
"found himself at the head of his section, later his company. \n"
"\n"
"Affected to law enforcement at Oa’s gallery during the goblin pretender "
"events, Boxa found himself face to face with goblin attackers that were "
"besieging the Iron Tower of Udxatfe and he beat them alone to flight, "
"sending with only some exceptions all his men to help defend the mines. Few "
"days later, he vanquished two full sections that were trying to pass Udxatfe "
"to reach the Eastern Kingdom and successfully contained the goblin threat to "
"the bay until these lasts finally retreat.\n"
"\n"
"Officially announcing his resignation from the army, he became the guardian "
"of the Western Kingdom, ruling the fortifications and the security of "
"Udxatfe and becoming the owner of the kingdom’s mines. Now retired, he is "
"one of the most respected strategists of the legion and is frequently "
"consulted officious ruler of south of Udxatfe."
msgstr ""
"Buxo Iova tiene la distinción de haber sido declarado muerto más veces que "
"cualquier otro soldado en la historia de la 10.ª Legión. En el paso de "
"Yooradweak, se decía que atacantes goblins lo habían derrotado, mientras que "
"tres días después él los ponía en fuga. Luego fue declarado muerto en una "
"tormenta de nieve mientras buscaba a Caprine, su querida mula, para "
"finalmente regresar una semana después, hambriento y molesto por un agujero "
"en su zapato. \n"
"\n"
"Para sus aliados, las historias sobre su muerte son entretenimiento. Para "
"sus enemigos, el objeto de su deseo. En su opinión, la muerte solo vendrá "
"por él cuando esté aburrido o cansado de la vida, ¡y más le vale a la Parca "
"traer refuerzos! \n"
"\n"
"Criado por una antigua cocinera de la 10.ª Legión, Buxo partió al oeste de "
"Idaamub como guía del sínodo ofita a los 16 años. Más tarde llegó al "
"castillo de Idaamub y presentó una carta que ordenaba darle el puesto de su "
"madre, pero resultó ser peor cocinero que soldado y pronto se encontró al "
"mando de su sección y luego de su compañía. \n"
"\n"
"Asignado al cumplimiento de la ley en la galería de Oa durante los eventos "
"del pretendiente goblin, Buxo se encontró cara a cara con atacantes goblins "
"que asediaban la Torre de Hierro de Udxatfe y los puso en fuga él solo, "
"enviando —con pocas excepciones— a todos sus hombres a ayudar a defender las "
"minas. Pocos días después, derrotó a dos secciones completas que intentaban "
"pasar por Udxatfe para llegar al Reino Oriental y logró contener la amenaza "
"goblin en la bahía hasta que finalmente se retiraron.\n"
"\n"
"Al anunciar oficialmente su renuncia al ejército, se convirtió en el "
"guardián del Reino Occidental, controlando las fortificaciones y la "
"seguridad de Udxatfe y convirtiéndose en el dueño de las minas del reino. "
"Ahora retirado, es uno de los estrategas más respetados de la legión y es "
"consultado frecuentemente como gobernante oficioso del sur de Udxatfe."

